{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a2634d7-1047-4bb2-8091-200ad8e2965b","content":"No repo-specific docs here, but I can give you the recommended MSTest setup directly.\n\n## 1. Simplest project file with MSTest.Sdk\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` bundles MSTest runner, framework, and analyzers — no extra `<PackageReference>` needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd a `.runsettings` file (or an `AssemblyInfo.cs`). The simplest way is an assembly-level attribute:\n\n```csharp\n// Properties/AssemblyInfo.cs\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test **methods** in parallel. Use `ExecutionScope.ClassLevel` if you want parallelism only across classes (methods within a class run sequentially).\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_And_Read_Back()\n    {\n        // This class runs sequentially, after all parallel tests finish\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Update_Existing_Record()\n    {\n        // Also sequential\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key behavior:** `[DoNotParallelize]` classes run **after** all parallelized tests complete, and their methods execute one at a time.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| SDK | `MSTest.Sdk/3.8` — single-line, batteries-included |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential opt-out | `[DoNotParallelize]` on specific classes |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7fbda85d-e5d4-448f-976c-97c43e976d93","outputTokens":482,"requestId":"EBC6:1F9B94:7CF13E:85048B:6A044F0E"},"id":"5aaaf177-1f09-41e5-be49-568134605d09","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:14:50.961Z","parentId":"514f7215-d733-4ae7-b